The paper deals with an energy-efficient scheduling problem in which jobs need to be executed while minimizing energy usage and ensuring that each job is finished within its deadline. This problem involves dynamic speed scaling with a sleep state, which is a common topic in computer science research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AL (Computational Complexity and Cryptography), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.PF (Performance).
